### 1.2 — Initial assessment

When the user asked to "make a GeoJSON map", the naive approach would be:

> ❌ **Trace polygons from screenshots** — This would require manual digitization of 95+ screenshots, visually tracing each red boundary outline and converting pixel coordinates to lat/lng. Extremely tedious, error-prone, and would take days.

Instead, I investigated whether the **source data** (the CDMA GIS portal) exposed an API with machine-readable boundary data.

> [!TIP]
> **Key insight:** If a website renders polygons on a map, the polygon coordinate data must exist somewhere — either embedded in the page source, loaded via API, or hardcoded in a JavaScript bundle. The goal is to find that data source.

